1" href="https://newsroom.spotify.com/2023-06-20/trevor-noah-hosts-spotify-original-podcast-comedy-launching-2023/">深入和随心所欲</a>”的讨论。</p><p>这一消息是在诺亚和 Spotify 联合创始人兼首席执行官丹尼尔·埃克 (Daniel Ek) 在戛纳创意节上就作为创作者与观众建立联系的对话中发布的。诺亚说，他很高兴能“与世界上一些最迷人的人进行有趣而有意义的对话。我们也可能会解决人类曾经面临的每一个问题，所以你肯定想加入我们的每一集。”</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>诺亚将在世界任何地方录制播客的能力归功于吸引他进入媒体的原因之一。这种情绪反映了他在七年后 <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://money.yahoo.com/trevor-noah-net-worth-no-180008925.html">离开<em>The Daily Show 的</em>部分原因</a>：“我怀念学习其他语言、去其他国家和参加演出。我怀念无处不在，无所不能。”</p><p>这一消息是在<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/spotify-ends-its-podcast-deal-with-harry-and-meghan-142710519.html">Spotify 与苏塞克斯公爵和公爵夫人分道扬镳</a>几天后传出的。据报道，这笔价值 2500 万美元的交易导致在三年内创建了一个播客， <em>Archetypes</em> 。在 12 集中，梅根·马克尔采访了包括诺亚在内的知名人士，了解女性面临的刻板印象。与 Spotify 独有的<em>Archetypes</em>不同，Noah 即将推出的播客将在其他平台上提供。</p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/trevor-noah-is-launching-a-weekly-talk-show-podcast-on-spotify-113516329.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/trevor-noah-is-launching-a-weekly-talk-show-podcast-on-spotify-113516329.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 8574bc6e-5e39-487a-9dcb-8538ab52032d</guid><dc:creator>莎拉菲尔丁</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Tue, 20 Jun 2023 11:35:16 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687258942</ingested><modified> 2023-06-20T11:02:26+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Sarah Fielding]]></category><media:content height="723" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/0f56a140-0f50-11ee-bdfe-462adaf41504" width="1236"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="723" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/0f56a140-0f50-11ee-bdfe-462adaf41504" width="1236"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Spotify]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Trevor Noah holds a microphone with Spotify logo on it and a flowered background behind him.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Trevor Noah Spotify]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[The Morning After: The verdict on Google’s Pixel Tablet]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>也许 Android 平板电脑终究还没有死。也许他们只需要一个智能显示底座和一个迷人的支架/衣架……让它们更实用。根据 Engadget 的 Cherlynn Low 的说法，500 美元的 Pixel Tablet 并不是一款特别令人兴奋的平板电脑，但它<em>是</em>一款引人入胜的智能显示器。</p><figure> <a href="https://www.engadget.com/google-pixel-tablet-review-clever-accessories-transform-an-unexciting-tablet-070147119.html"><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/14f881c0-0f43-11ee-bfbf-b7d68a8a4e0a" style="height:453px;width:675px;" alt="三甲基丙烯酸甲酯" data-uuid="4d81f7aa-37ee-39be-a2df-16d274da5536"></a><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> <a href="https://www.engadget.com/google-pixel-tablet-review-clever-accessories-transform-an-unexciting-tablet-070147119.html">Engadget</a></div></figure><p>凭借其充电扬声器底座和 80 美元的盒子，谷歌提出了一个更具吸引力的提议。有一些不寻常的怪癖，尤其是在 Chromecasting 方面，但它是一款时尚的混合显示器，有很多优点。在<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-pixel-tablet-review-clever-accessories-transform-an-unexciting-tablet-070147119.html">此处</a>查看完整评论。</p><p> – 马特·史密斯</p><p><em>The Morning After 不仅仅是一份</em><a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/about/newsletter/"><em>时事通讯</em></a><em>——它还是一个每日播客。</em> <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-08-01-engadget-podcasts.html"><em>在这里订阅</em></a><em>，获取周一至周五的每日音频简报</em><em>。</em></p><p></p><h3>你可能错过的最重要的故事</h3><h3></h3><p><a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/apple-watch-series-8-is-back-on-sale-for-329-141547847.html">Apple Watch Series 8 重新开售，售价 329 美元</a></p><p><a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-smart-scale-160033523.html">2023 年最好的智能秤</a></p><p><a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/operas-generative-ai-infused-browser-is-ready-for-the-masses-070013098.html">Opera 的生成式人工智能浏览器已为大众做好准备</a></p><p></p><h2><a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-fcc-is-preparing-to-take-a-fresh-look-at-internet-data-caps-084245899.html">FCC 正准备“重新审视”互联网数据上限</a></h2><h3>它还在考虑是否可以合法地对他们“采取行动”。</h3><h3></h3><p>联邦通信委员会 (FCC) 主席杰西卡·罗森沃塞尔 (Jessica Rosenworcel) 希望就互联网数据上限对消费者的影响发布正式的调查通知。监管机构还将考虑“采取行动”以确保数据上限不会损害竞争或影响宽带服务的访问。</p><p> Rosenworcel 说：“互联网接入不再是可有可无的东西，而是每个人、任何地方都需要拥有的东西。” “当我们需要访问互联网时，我们不会考虑完成一项任务需要多少数据，我们只知道它需要完成。”不过，Rosenworcel 目前无法对数据上限采取任何行动。FCC 目前只有四名成员（两名民主党人和两名共和党人），因为参议院拒绝确认拜登总统的第一位提名人 Gigi Sohn，她随后退出了她的名字供考虑。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:8;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-fcc-is-preparing-to-take-a-fresh-look-at-internet-data-caps-084245899.html"><strong>继续阅读。</strong></a></p><p></p><h2> <a data-i13n="cpos:9;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/best-e-ink-tablet-130037939.html%20https://www.engadget.com/...">2023 年最好的 E Ink 平板电脑</a></h2><h3>随心所欲地涂鸦。 </h3><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/14f881c0-0f43-11ee-beef-2d8b6fd8809e" style="height:447px;width:675px;" alt="三甲基丙烯酸甲酯" data-uuid="26a90059-e2d3-3201-8d97-1bbf8216d128"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Engadget</div></figure><p> E Ink 平板电脑结合了在普通笔记本上书写的感觉和数字化文档的许多便利性。有了它们，您可以随身携带并在一台设备上涂写所有笔记。不过，与普通平板电脑和手写笔不同，E Ink 平板电脑远没有那么普遍——它们仍然只对极少数特定人群值得购买。那是你吗？如果是这样，您最好的选择是什么？</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:10;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/black-mirror-season-six-review-netflix-130015184.htmlhttps://www.engadget.com/best-e-ink-tablet-130037939.html"><strong>继续阅读。</strong></a></p><p></p><h2> <a data-i13n="cpos:11;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/black-mirror-season-six-review-netflix-130015184.html">“黑镜”在我们现代的地狱景观中找到新的生命</a></h2><h3>第六季为该系列带来了大量新旧元素。</h3><h3></h3><p>自<em>《黑镜</em>》上一季以来的三年里，我们经历了一场全球性流行病，目睹了一位美国总统引发了对国会大厦的暴徒袭击，我们<em>到处都</em>在谈论人工智能。根据 Engadget 的德文德拉·哈达瓦 (​​Devindra Hardawar) 的说法，上周在 Netflix 上线的<em>《黑镜》(Black Mirror)</em>第六季是该系列的最佳作品：令人震惊、尖锐而且时常搞笑。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:12;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/black-mirror-season-six-review-netflix-130015184.html"><strong>继续阅读。</strong></a></p><p></p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><h2> <a data-i13n="cpos:13;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-brings-its-self-repair-program-to-the-uk-125913488.html">三星将其自我修复计划带到英国</a></h2><h3>Galaxy S20、21 和 S22 的所有者可以更换屏幕、后玻璃和充电端口。</h3><h3></h3><p>继去年在美国推出后，三星宣布其自助维修计划现已在英国和其他欧洲国家推出。用户可以获得修复受支持设备所需的工具和部件，即 Galaxy S20、S21 和 S22 智能手机，以及 Galaxy Book Pro 普通版和 Galaxy Book Pro 360 笔记本电脑。</p><p>除英国外，该计划还将在比利时、法国、意大利、荷兰、波兰、西班牙和瑞典推出。三星在美国与 iFixit 合作，但零件分销商 ASWO 和 2Service 将负责维修套件在欧洲的销售和分销。</p><p> <a data-i13n="cpos:14;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/samsung-brings-its-self-repair-program-to-the-uk-125913488.html"><strong>继续阅读。</strong></a></p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/the-morning-after-the-verdict-on-googles-pixel-tablet-111558309.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/the-morning-after-the-verdict-on-googles-pixel-tablet-111558309.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> ececf2bb-84d5-4826-bef5-937c24d29c1d</guid><dc:creator>马特·史密斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Tue, 20 Jun 2023 11:15:58 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687256165</ingested><modified> 2023-06-20T10:16:12+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Consumer Discretionary]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mat Smith]]></category><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/4cb57850-0f22-11ee-9bff-58fae9e71438" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1333" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/4cb57850-0f22-11ee-9bff-58fae9e71438" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Photo by Cherlynn Low / Engadget]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[The Pixel Tablet on a walnut dresser, with various items behind it. The top two drawers are in view.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Google Pixel Tablet]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Philips Hue lights are getting brightness balancing and better motion sensor automations]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>制造商 Signify <a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.signify.com/en-gb/our-company/news/press-releases/2023/20230620-from-big-to-small-philips-hue-continuously-innovates-to-help-you-personalize-your-home">宣布</a>，<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/tag/philips-hue/">飞利浦 Hue</a>推出了一些新功能，可以更轻松地匹配不同灯的亮度级别并微调运动传感器自动化。该公司还推出了三款新的照明产品，包括一个灯泡和两个面板，但似乎只在英国推出。</p><p>第一个更新称为亮度平衡器，是应用户要求开发的。如果您在同一个房间里有多个不同亮度级别的灯，该功能可以更容易地通过调暗明亮的灯光而不是昏暗的灯光来平衡它们。飞利浦说，这允许用户创造均匀的照明或“当你同步到你的电视、电影、游戏或音乐时，决定房间的哪一部分得到聚光灯”。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>另一个功能增强了飞利浦 Hue 运动传感器的功能。目前，飞利浦 Hue 桥接应用程序仅支持两个时间段，用于在传感器检测到运动时自动调整光照条件，例如早上凉爽和晚上温暖。通过更新，您将能够根据运动传感器自定义照明条件，检测到运动时总共有 10 倍。 “可以选择自然光场景作为这些时间段的一部分，以模仿全天的太阳，”该公司指出。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/106970d0-0f50-11ee-9eff-42b0fb29d0b9" style="height:1456px;width:2000px;" alt="飞利浦 Hue 灯正在获得亮度平衡和更好的运动传感器自动化" data-uuid="e37e21c2-5dfa-3b01-b764-0a4e00d5ffe1"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">飞利浦</div></figure><p>在英国，飞利浦还推出了 E14 lustre 灯泡（1 件装 30 英镑或 3 件装 55 英镑），基于其最小的高尔夫球大小的灯泡，提供数百万种白色和彩色光。它还有一对新的面板灯，300x300mm 型号的 Surimu 面板起价 210 英镑，以及黑色的 Aurelle（上图），300x300 面板的起价为 150 英镑。所有的灯今天都抵达英国，新的 Hue Bridge 功能将于 2023 年第三季度推出。</p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/philips-hue-lights-are-getting-brightness-balancing-and-better-motion-sensor-automations-105005772.html?src=rss]] >; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/philips-hue-lights-are-getting-brightness-balancing-and-better-motion-sensor-automations-105005772.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> b78d1557-c6f3-4b19-9b97-47915a5a4d2f</guid><dc:creator>史蒂夫登特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Tue, 20 Jun 2023 10:50:05 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687254856</ingested><modified> 2023-06-20T09:54:19+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Steve Dent]]></category><media:content height="1364" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/341c6750-0f49-11ee-b44f-6fb9fcd5102c" width="2000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1364" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/341c6750-0f49-11ee-b44f-6fb9fcd5102c" width="2000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[Philips]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Philips Hue lights are getting brightness balancing and better motion sensor automations]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Philips Hue lights are getting brightness balancing and better motion sensor automations]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Terraform Labs founder Do Kwon handed four month sentence in Montenegro]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Terraform Labs 创始人<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/sec-charges-terraform-and-ceo-with-fraud-145347680.html">Do Kwon 因一项计划在去年该公司的加密货币暴跌时使投资者损失 400 亿美元而受到韩国和美国的通缉</a>——但目前，他将被关进黑山监狱。据当地报纸<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.vijesti.me/vijesti/crna-hronika/661784/do-kvon-i-hond-can-jun-osudjeni-na-po-cetiri-mjeseca-zatvora"><em>Vijesti</em>报道，</a> Kwon 因伪造官方文件而被判有罪，并在 3 月下旬被捕后被判入狱四个月，当时他试图用假哥斯达黎加护照从波德戈里察机场登上飞往迪拜的航班。 Terraform Labs 前财务官 Han Chang-joon 也因同样的罪名受到指控和判刑。两人还被发现在行李中伪造了比利时护照，以及韩国和美国当局要求搜查的电脑。</p><p> Kwon 和他的同事将 TerraUSD 和 Luna 作为与美元挂钩的稳定币进行营销，据称可以让它们更加<em>稳定</em>。他们<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/the-morning-after-the-world-of-cryptocurrency-continues-to-wobble-111526550.html">于 2022 年 5 月倒闭</a>，并带走了许多投资者一生的积蓄，这些人随后投诉 Kwon 实施了庞氏骗局。韩国于去年 9 月首次宣布对 Kwon 和五名同伙发出逮捕令，但他、他的家人和 Terraform Labs 的一些财务员工已经逃往该公司注册地新加坡。应韩国当局的要求，国际刑警组织很快将权某列入“ <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/south-korean-prosecutors-interpol-terraform-labs-ceo-do-kwon-060719940.html">红色通缉令</a>”名单，向全球执法部门发出逮捕他的信号。黑山当局将此作为逮捕权的另一个原因。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>美国证券交易委员会在 2 月份<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.sec.gov/news/press-release/2023-32">指控 Kwon</a>未能“按照要求向公众提供大量加密资产证券的完整、公平和真实的披露，尤其是 LUNA 和 Terra USD。我们还指控他们犯有欺诈行为在给投资者造成毁灭性损失之前，通过重复虚假和误导性陈述来建立信任。”权某被捕后，位于曼哈顿的美国地方法院公开发布了对权某八项罪名的起诉书，其中包括证券欺诈和共谋罪。</p><p>尽管黑山与美国或韩国没有引渡条约，但这个想法仍在讨论之中。在决定是否以及如何处理两国的引渡请求时，黑山当局将他们的拘留时间延长了六个月后不久，就判处了四个月的监禁。</p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/terraform-labs-founder-do-kwon-handed-four-month-sentence-in-montenegro-100507468.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/terraform-labs-founder-do-kwon-handed-four-month-sentence-in-montenegro-100507468.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 7562129d-e797-468e-b1eb-51276c04ca82</guid><dc:creator>莎拉菲尔丁</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Tue, 20 Jun 2023 10:05:07 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687254495</ingested><modified> 2023-06-20T09:48:24+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Society & Culture]]></category><category><![CDATA[Crime & Justice]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Sarah Fielding]]></category><media:content height="3400" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-05/7c22d6c0-dab0-11ec-bd7b-9d0f952fbb91" width="5500"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3400" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-05/7c22d6c0-dab0-11ec-bd7b-9d0f952fbb91" width="5500"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[naito8 via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Terra (LUNA) crypto currency token logo on coin technology themed design.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Terra (LUNA) crypto currency token logo on coin technology themed design.]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Vimeo's new AI-powered editing tools are designed for beginners]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/vimeo-will-stop-supporting-its-tv-apps-on-june-27th-194846561.html">Vimeo</a>是最新<a data-i13n="elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Vimeo;elmt:;cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=7d99dc20-7530-4df8-98e2-2f910e52ec89&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Vimeo&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI3ZDk5ZGMyMC03NTMwLTRkZjgtOThlMi0yZjkxMGU1MmVjODkiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly92aW1lby5jb20vY2FtcGFpZ25zL29uZS10YWtlLXZpZGVvIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJmMGFhZmJiNy01N2U1LTQ0MmQtOTNmNC04OTMxNmI3ZGM5YjAifQ&amp;signature=AQAAASIuHPgG1CdwhCxbugBM7dw6y_nw4p_pUdE7pbeGuFhW&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fvimeo.com%2Fcampaigns%2Fone-take-video" class="rapid-with-clickid">推出自己的人工智能工具的</a>公司之一，正如您所料，他们致力于让创作者更轻松地编辑他们的视频。该视频托管平台表示，大多数人“缺乏有效创建和编辑视频的技能、时间或资源”，而这些功能旨在消除这些障碍。</p><p>也许这三个新的 AI 工具中最有用的是基于文本的视频编辑器，它可以自动删除长时间的停顿和视频中带有填充词的部分，例如“嗯”和“啊”，只需单击一下。用户还可以通过在该工具生成的文字记录中搜索某些词，然后单击删除，轻松删除他们想要的视频的任何部分。如果他们想为社交媒体制作短片，他们可以在文字记录中搜索特定的词，突出显示并右键单击该词、句子或段落，然后选择“只保留这个”。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> Vimeo 还推出了一个脚本生成器，可以根据用户编写的文本提示、预期的视频长度和他们选择的“基调”（例如自信、有趣或随意）来生成完整的脚本。据<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://techcrunch.com/2023/06/19/vimeo-introduces-a-trio-of-ai-powered-editing-features/"><em>TechCrunch</em></a>称，它由 OpenAI 的 GPT 技术提供支持，通过其 API 成为编辑套件的一部分。最后，该公司推出了一种屏幕提词器，可以显示带有用户设置的字体大小和步调的脚本。它可以帮助创作者在保持与相机的目光接触的同时保持脚本。</p><p>所有这三种工具都将在 7 月作为 Vimeo 标准和专业订阅计划的一部分提供。虽然用户可以在这些计划的 7 天试用期内对其进行测试，但他们最终必须每月至少支付 20 美元（按年计费）才能继续使用它们。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/31f75e10-0f41-11ee-b9fd-8a9f10713b0f" style="height:824px;width:1600px;" alt="Vimeo 基于文本的视频编辑器的屏幕截图。左边是一个文本框，右边是一个穿着蓝色马球的男人的视频。他面前有一张桌子，上面放着马克杯和彩色纸。" data-uuid="902ad00a-9578-32c5-9fe8-cb69e8022298"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit">维密欧</div></figure><p></p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/vimeos-new-ai-powered-editing-tools-are-designed-for-beginners-091529203.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/vimeos-new-ai-powered-editing-tools-are-designed-for-beginners-091529203.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> f0aafbb7-57e5-442d-93f4-89316b7dc9b0</guid><dc:creator>玛丽拉月亮</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Tue, 20 Jun 2023 09:15:29 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687251456</ingested><modified> 2023-06-20T08:57:46+00:00</modified><category><![CDATA[Software]]></category><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="3600" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/e28d78f0-0f40-11ee-8b9f-78d914ec4276" width="5400"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="3600" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/e28d78f0-0f40-11ee-8b9f-78d914ec4276" width="5400"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ASSOCIATED PRESS]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Anjali Sud, CEO of Vimeo, speaks during the company's direct listing on Nasdaq, Tuesday, May 25, 2021, in New York. The online video and software company is a spinoff from IAC. (AP Photo/Mark Lennihan)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Financial Markets Wall Street Vimeo]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[WhatsApp can now automatically silence unknown callers]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>该公司<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://blog.whatsapp.com/new-privacy-features-silence-unknown-callers-and-privacy-checkup">宣布</a>，通过新的更新，WhatsApp 希望减少骚扰电话的烦扰，并让用户选择最佳的隐私设置。第一个功能，称为静音未知呼叫者，正是这样做的 - 电话不会在您的手机上响铃，但会出现在您的呼叫列表中，以防呼叫很重要但您必须响应。对于大多数用户来说，这应该提供实用性和隐私性的良好结合。</p><p>谈到隐私，WhatsApp 还推出了一项名为“隐私检查”的功能。 “在你的隐私设置中选择‘开始检查’将引导你通过多个隐私层，加强你的消息、电话和个人信息的安全性，”该公司表示。这样做会提供诸如“选择谁可以联系你”、“控制你的个人信息”、“为你的聊天增加更多隐私”和“为你的帐户增加更多保护”等选项。 </p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/551543b0-0f3e-11ee-bffd-039a3610fee9" style="height:4321px;width:7680px;" alt="WhatsApp 的新隐私功能包括让未知来电者静音" data-uuid="7110d138-a60e-3655-946d-3ebd0fd36478"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> WhatsApp的</div></figure><p>WhatsApp 还发布了一段感人的新视频，鼓励用户查看他们可能关心的朋友。该公司甚至提供了一个模板：“嘿，我一直在想你。如果你需要聊天，我就在这里。除了我们，其他人都看不到。你也可以打开消失模式或使用聊天锁特征。”这是 WhatsApp 推广关键隐私功能的一种方式——例如，聊天锁是<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/whatsapps-new-privacy-feature-locks-sensitive-chats-and-hides-them-from-notifications-181005512.html">上个月刚刚推出的</a>。正如许多评论者在推出时<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.facebook.com/zuck/posts/10115120657003951">指出的</a>那样，它也可能与聊天锁是<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/may/17/whatsapp-now-lets-you-hide-your-messages-from-prying-eyes-but-is-chat-lock-a-cheaters-charter">为作弊者量身定做的</a>概念背道而驰。新功能现已推出。 </p><div id="ad20ee4988aa4745aa1c370b71ea134f"><div style="left:0;width:100%;height:0;position:relative;padding-bottom:56.25%;"><iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/JXHqaCWsaWI?rel=0" style="top:0;left:0;width:100%;height:100%;position:absolute;border:0;" allowfullscreen="" scrolling="no"></iframe></div></div><p></p>本文最初出现在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/whatsapp-can-now-automatically-silence-unknown-callers-082512152.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/whatsapp-can-now-automatically-silence-unknown-callers-082512152.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> c5ce835d-3829-42de-af4b-c4ac435a2369</guid><dc:creator>史蒂夫登特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Tue, 20 Jun 2023 08:25:12 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687249514</ingested><modified> 2023-06-20T08:25:17+00:00</modified><category><![CDATA[Software]]></category><category><![CDATA[Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[Arts & Entertainment]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Steve Dent]]></category><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/fc7e9250-0f39-11ee-bff2-99280e6fc95e" width="1920"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="1080" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/fc7e9250-0f39-11ee-bff2-99280e6fc95e" width="1920"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[WhatsApp]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[WhatsApp's new privacy features include the silencing of unknown callers]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[WhatsApp's new privacy features include the silencing of unknown callers]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Google Pixel Tablet review: Clever accessories transform an unexciting tablet]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p> Pixel 平板电脑就像一个情绪不稳定的伙伴。在美好的日子里，它可靠且乐于助人，随时准备倾听并支持我。不过，时不时地，我会因为它的前后矛盾和混杂的信息而感到气愤和恼火。这可能是因为谷歌最新的平板电脑/智能显示器混合产品跨越了两个产品类别：一个是它擅长的领域，另一个是它恰到好处的领域。作为智能显示器，Pixel 平板电脑大放异彩。它有一个有用的仪表板、一个易于阅读的界面和令人印象深刻的音频质量。作为平板电脑，它很不错，但并没有让我失望。加上谷歌制造的外壳，它立即变得更加通用。 Pixel Tablet <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1;elm:affiliate_link;sellerN:Amazon;elmt:;" href="https://shopping.yahoo.com/rdlw?merchantId=66ea567a-c987-4c2e-a2ff-02904efde6ea&amp;siteId=us-engadget&amp;pageId=1p-autolink&amp;featureId=text-link&amp;merchantName=Amazon&amp;custData=eyJzb3VyY2VOYW1lIjoiV2ViLURlc2t0b3AtVmVyaXpvbiIsInN0b3JlSWQiOiI2NmVhNTY3YS1jOTg3LTRjMmUtYTJmZi0wMjkwNGVmZGU2ZWEiLCJsYW5kaW5nVXJsIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYW1hem9uLmNvbS9Hb29nbGUtUGl4ZWwtVGFibGV0LUNoYXJnaW5nLVNwZWFrZXIvZHAvQjBDMVNMRDFQSy8_dGFnPWdkZ3QwYy1wLW8tMTNnLTIwIiwiY29udGVudFV1aWQiOiJmNTY3YmUyNS03YTZjLTQ0MWItOTA5Mi1hNmVmMjIyZDY3YWUifQ&amp;signature=AQAAAZmjPYkRk1vs3hG9HFLXTA3kNO-QsS98Z51qtbGPPnD5&amp;gcReferrer=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FGoogle-Pixel-Tablet-Charging-Speaker%2Fdp%2FB0C1SLD1PK%2F">售价 500 美元</a>，附带充电扬声器底座，是两种价格合理的产品的完美结合。</p><h3>硬件与设计</h3><p>如果我们计算一下，因为您可以以每个 120 美元的价格购买额外的扬声器底座，这意味着平板电脑基本上需要 380 美元。但它肯定<em>不像</em>是低于 400 美元的设备。虽然纳米陶瓷涂层看起来并不出众，但它给背面带来了玻璃般的感觉，让人感觉更贵。令人印象深刻的是，Pixel 平板电脑的重量仅为 1.09 磅（493 克），比 Galaxy Tab S8 和 OnePlus Pad 更轻。不过，它仍然比 iPad Air 重。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>谷歌发送的审查单位是玫瑰色选项，令人愉快且无害。它是三种颜色中最令人兴奋的（黑色和白色是另外两种，所以这没什么好说的），它与我的生活空间融为一体（或平淡无奇）。我更喜欢 OnePlus Pad 的绿色色调，但值得注意的是，当我将 Pixel Tablet 交给我的同事 Nathan Ingraham 时，他最近评论了 480 美元的 OnePlus Pad，他认为谷歌的设备感觉更高级。 </p><p><core-commerce id="1c0ff4a7c4104e8bbd71cd5a746f31c4" data-type="product-list"></p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/2afd92b0-0f22-11ee-9fbd-cf12a1e1d5d2" alt="胡桃木梳妆台上 Pixel 平板电脑的侧视图，显示左侧边缘的 USB-C 端口。它停靠在扬声器底座上，并带有保护套。" data-uuid="8e4288a2-1e70-371b-8eb1-ba4a54c960db"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Cherlynn Low / Engadget 摄</div></figure><p>Pixel 平板电脑与其他近期 Android 平板电脑的真正区别在于，它设计用于连接到充电扬声器底座并兼作智能显示器。现在，我们不要忘记其他设备也能做到这一点，主要是<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2018-06-28-amazon-fire-hd-10-for-kids-show-mode-dock.html">亚马逊</a>和<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-01-08-lenovo-smart-tab-hands-on.html">联想的</a>大量平板电脑，它们具有显示模式，可以将它们变成支持 Alexa 的屏幕。但这是谷歌生态系统的第一次。</p><p>不过，在我了解 Pixel 平板电脑如何用作智能显示器之前，先简要介绍一下它的外观。如果您看过一款 Google Home 产品，那么您基本上已经看过所有这些产品。 Pixel 平板电脑与扬声器对接时，看起来几乎与 Nest Hub Max 完全一样。它具有相同的圆角矩形形状，11 英寸屏幕周围有白色边框，底座采用与公司其他智能家居产品类似的网眼织物覆盖。同样，它既无害又令人愉悦，但不会像西榆树或 Article 装饰品那样打动我的心。 （我知道，我很基础。）</p><h3>作为智能显示器</h3><p>我很高兴能将 Pixel 平板电脑放在我卧室的抽屉柜上（来自 Article），这样我就可以在上面看节目，而不必购买第二台电视或在手机上播放。谷歌警告不要在一个房间里安装多个支持智能助理的设备，我应该断开床头柜上已有的 Nest Mini 扬声器。但在我把它们都放在那儿的几天里，它并没有造成太多问题——当我站在靠近小扬声器的地方说“嘿谷歌”时，Pixel 平板电脑上播放的视频的音量会降低，所以可以听到我的声音更清楚。</p><p>一周后，我现在可以自信地取出 Nest Mini。 Pixel Tablet 不仅能听懂我的命令，还能提供更好的音频质量，而且更加实用。这是一个显而易见的陈述——当然，显示器比单独的扬声器更通用。但我对扬声器基座的声音改善感到惊讶，因为它并不比 Mini 大多少。它为我无休止地播放 The Weeknd 和周杰伦的播放列表提供了充足的低音，而高音和声音听起来清脆。 </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/4cb57850-0f22-11ee-9bff-58fae9e71438" alt="胡桃木梳妆台上的 Pixel 平板电脑，后面有各种物品。可以看到最上面的两个抽屉。" data-uuid="3a87519a-4e2a-3d2e-b7e5-af5601028c7a"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Cherlynn Low / Engadget 摄</div></figure><p>我不是那种会在智能显示器前摆弄我连接的家庭控制装置的人，我也不会经常有人过来，以至于我需要某种对客人友好的界面来打开我的灯。不过，对于那些这样做的人来说，Pixel 平板电脑的集线器模式可能非常有用。点击锁定屏幕左下角的房屋图标会弹出一个仪表板，显示您家中的所有设备，您将能够监控摄像头信号、打开电灯等等。只要您正确设置了权限，客人还可以要求智能助理设置定时器、闹钟、播放音乐等，而无需解锁您的平板电脑。</p><p>除了没有访客之外，无论房间多暗或多亮，只要我踏进房间，就很容易看到 Pixel 平板电脑屏幕上的东西。到了晚上，显示屏会进入昏暗模式，以大字体显示时间，但不会太亮以至于灼伤你的视网膜。因为我的梳妆台在离门最远的角落，所以不用眯着眼睛看时间、倒计时或温度等信息真是太好了。就像一个真正的自恋者一样，我还设置了 Pixel Tablet 以显示我最喜欢的人（主要是我）的轮换照片流。</p><p>顺便说一下，这并不是 Pixel 平板电脑独有的。 Nest Hub Max 的计时器和其他信息也有类似的更大字体，而相框功能基本上是任何智能显示器的主要功能。</p><p>不过，回到我想使用这款平板电脑的主要目的：作为电视替代品。由于它是第一款成为 Chromecast 接收器的平板电脑，因此当它从 YouTube、Disney+、Hulu 等应用程序流式传输时，您可以通过手机远程控制 Pixel 平板电脑。当然，其他更大的智能显示器（如 Nest Hub Max）也可以做到这一点，并且由于在 Pixel 平板电脑未连接时这不起作用，因此它不是真正可以投射到的<em>平板电脑</em>。 We&#39;re getting really technical with definitions here, but in practical use, it means you can&#39;t cast to the Pixel Tablet when you have it hanging or propped up elsewhere in your home, for example. It&#39;s not a problem, but it limits the versatility of this feature. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/8251fce0-0f22-11ee-95a7-6b99a548653e" alt="Pixel 平板电脑的侧视图，在其屏幕上显示两张照片作为相框功能的一部分。" data-uuid="6d240868-ce3a-3b07-9515-38a283afab55"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Cherlynn Low / Engadget</div></figure><p> Interestingly, Netflix doesn&#39;t support Chromecasting to the tablet, unlike the other apps. It&#39;s all the more strange considering it works on Google&#39;s other larger smart displays. I also encountered a bug where YouTube refused to cast videos from a specific channel, saying they weren&#39;t allowed when I was in Restricted mode. But none of the devices I was logged into had that setting enabled. Other reviewers I spoke to didn&#39;t have this issue, so this might be a bug specific to my setup.</p><p> It did infuriate me though, because it&#39;s easier to Chromecast my favorite commentary videos since I can skip ads or add more titles without having to drag myself out of bed. Sadly, I had to do just that since I ended up playing them via the native YouTube app. My hatred for this bug grew each time I had to get out and hit “Skip ads” on the screen. (No, you won&#39;t convince me to get YouTube Premium.) This small bug aside, though, Chromecasting is a nice touch on the Pixel Tablet, even if it isn&#39;t unique.</p><p> I have multiple Google Home products in my apartment, and some of my issues with the Pixel Tablet as a smart display are ecosystem-wide instead of specific to the device. For instance, when I set up an Automation through the Home app, I wanted it so that saying “I&#39;m home” would start a playlist on the pair of Nest Audios in my living room. However, at the moment only the device that heard you can be the one playing the music. You can&#39;t decide which of your connected speakers does the action.</p><p> Depending on the way your home is set up, like if you have a Mini in your entryway and prefer your beefier living room system to be the output, this might be frustrating. Luckily for me, the correct devices heard me most of the time, and I almost always got my desired outcome. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/a5116770-0f22-11ee-bfbf-9c59a505056f" alt="胡桃木梳妆台上的 Pixel 平板电脑显示了处于 Hub 模式的智能家居仪表板。" data-uuid="71f720f8-e144-3eee-b43c-1b9c46270c83"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Cherlynn Low / Engadget</div></figure><p> That&#39;s more of a complaint about Google&#39;s smart home system instead of just the Pixel Tablet, which frankly I am pretty happy with. Not only is it a good connected display, but it&#39;s also useful as a second screen when sat next to my laptop.</p><p> Since it runs full Android, I can have apps like Solitaire or Slack open on it while I work on a review. You can also take video calls through Meet, Zoom, Teams or more, using the 8-megapixel webcam up top. The angle at which the speaker dock props up the tablet makes for a very unflattering shot, though. To mitigate that, Google built in an auto-framing feature that kicks in whenever you take a Meet call while connected to the base. It only works with Meet, though, so you&#39;ll have to rely on third-party apps to provide their own solutions.</p><p> I found that removing the tablet and propping it up with the kickstand on Google&#39;s case made for the best view. In fact, I&#39;m pretty much in love with this accessory. </p><section data-eng-breakout="a1bf7ebde92b41a4a37eccdd0db9c7fe" data-eng-breakout-type="e2ehero"><img class="e2ehero-url" src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/c91befa0-0f22-11ee-bf6b-e6e0783a7061" alt="The Pixel Tablet on a walnut dresser propped up by the silver kickstand on the back of its protective case."></section><h3> As a tablet</h3><p> Look, a kickstand on a tablet isn&#39;t a groundbreaking concept. Lenovo made tablets with built-in stands that also worked as hangers years ago, while Surface devices have featured similar mechanisms for ages. But neither Lenovo&#39;s Yoga Tablet nor any of the Surfaces doubled as smart displays. Google was also thoughtful enough to build the kickstand so that it wouldn&#39;t get in the way of attaching the tablet to the speaker. In fact, the ring-shaped kickstand almost perfectly encircles the dock when folded into the case.</p><p> What I love about the kickstand-hanger-combo is that it allows you to place the Tablet pretty much anywhere. So when I want to hang it off a kitchen cabinet to follow along with a recipe video or keep watching <em>Love Is Blind</em> for example, I can. And though the 2,560 x 1,600 LCD panel isn&#39;t as vibrant as the OLED on Samsung&#39;s Galaxy Tabs, it still produced crisp details and colorful images.</p><p> I&#39;ve waxed poetic about the case, but it&#39;s not without flaws. The way it wraps around the power button makes accessing the fingerprint sensor difficult. The cases Google sent us for review are pre-production samples, though, so it&#39;s possible the company will improve this before launch.</p><p> I also played endless rounds of Solitaire with the tablet propped up on my table while I had dinner and watched TV. That&#39;s honestly what most tablets are good for – entertainment – , but often not much else. Google does offer some multitasking features in Android, but it doesn&#39;t make a keyboard specifically for the Pixel Tablet. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/ff448790-0f22-11ee-bffa-912737b93bdc" alt="带有保护套的 Pixel 平板电脑插接在扬声器底座上。它折叠起来的银色支架是一个环绕扬声器的环。" data-uuid="d6e522a2-e909-3092-b640-73cd2dafa6ed"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Cherlynn Low / Engadget</div></figure><p> You can connect your own Bluetooth keyboard, of course, but Android L still isn&#39;t the best platform for productivity. Yes, you can run two apps side by side or drag and drop pictures between things like WhatsApp and Gmail. And plenty of first-party and third-party apps support this feature and are now optimized for larger screens. But quirks persist.</p><p> When you drag the vertical divider to resize apps, for example, you&#39;ll sometimes need to relaunch them. It happens often when you shrink something down from taking up half the screen to about a third. The system will ask you to tap a button to re-open it, at which point it changes to the smartphone version. Thankfully, relaunching an app doesn&#39;t take long, and when I had to do this with the New York Times crossword, it opened again exactly where I left off instead of forcing me to start over from the home page.</p><p> The new taskbar that Google introduced on the Pixel Tablet makes it easier to launch apps in split screen, though the gesture takes a bit to get used to. Like the row of predicted apps in the Android app drawer, this taskbar will study your habits and over time, start to surface things it suspects you want.</p><p> Another thing that the Pixel Tablet might be good for, in theory, is drawing and taking notes. Though Google does make a $30 stylus for the device, it did not send samples along with review units, so I wasn&#39;t able to test it for this review.</p><p> Here&#39;s the thing: I barely used the Pixel Tablet undocked. I rarely felt the need to pick it up, unless my phone was dead and I wanted to play more Solitaire. The upside of always placing the Tablet on its dock is that when I do want a larger screen for reading, more immersive gaming or watching movies on the go, the Tablet is always charged and ready for me. </p><figure><img src="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-06/2fe78c80-0f23-11ee-9ebf-e0173cdb2c69" alt="Pixel 平板电脑上的电源按钮特写，它被保护套覆盖着。" data-uuid="22aeae1c-3f26-3071-bebc-bfb2da53e6c9"><figcaption></figcaption><div class="photo-credit"> Photo by Cherlynn Low / Engadget</div></figure><p> Because of that, it was challenging to get a real sense of the day-to-day battery life. Whenever I was done with the few moments I needed the device, I instinctively placed it back on the dock, where it would slowly juice back up.</p><p> When you do need the tablet to last you longer than a few moments in your home, though, it&#39;s more than up to the task. On our video rundown battery test, the Pixel Tablet clocked 21 and a half hours at 50 percent brightness, which is more than the longest international nonstop flights.</p><p> If you ever do run out of juice, it takes the Pixel Tablet about three hours to get back to fully charged if you use a cable. On the speaker dock, Google optimizes charging to preserve battery life, maintaining it at about 90 percent instead of fully topping it off. I haven&#39;t measured if the charging speed here is slower than with a wire, especially since I&#39;m not usually in a hurry to pick the tablet back up after docking it.</p><h3> Wrap-up</h3><p> Maybe Android tablets aren&#39;t dead after all. Maybe all they needed was a dock to call home and kickstand/hanger that made them more functional. But, despite its name, the Pixel Tablet is far less exciting as a tablet than a smart display. With its charging speaker dock and $80 case, Google presents a far more compelling proposition for its latest product. And despite some quirks, I&#39;ve found life with the Pixel Tablet to be enjoyable, and most of its problems seem solvable. I can only hope Google keeps working on it and doesn&#39;t unceremoniously cast the Pixel Tablet into its graveyard of unloved products. With some software updates, there&#39;s a potentially bright future for the Pixel Tablet.</p> This article originally appeared on Engadget at https://www.engadget.com/google-pixel-tablet-review-clever-accessories-transform-an-unexciting-tablet-070147119.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/google-pixel-tablet-review-clever-accessories-transform-an-unexciting-tablet-070147119.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> f567be25-7a6c-441b-9092-a6ef222d67ae</guid><dc:creator> Cherlynn Low</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher> Engadget</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder> Engadget</dc:rightsholder><pubDate> Tue, 20 Jun 2023 07:01:47 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1687262860</ingested><modified> 2023-06-20T12:07:49+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Tablets]]></category><category><![CDATA[Technology & Electronics]]></category><category><![CDATA[Handheld & Connected Devices]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Cherlynn Low]]></category><media:content height="1342" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-image